WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:40.643 --> 00:43.393
<i>We've got a homicide,
possibly gang-related.</i>

00:43.477 --> 00:44.727
<i>York Hotel.</i>

00:44.810 --> 00:46.643
<i>Yeah, copy that, Control. 10-4.</i>

00:51.560 --> 00:53.310
York Hotel, as quick as you can.

00:54.060 --> 00:55.310
Thanks, sweetie.

01:17.060 --> 01:19.560
Hey, Frank, how about a freebie?

01:30.852 --> 01:31.977
Thanks.

02:22.477 --> 02:24.517
- Detective Crankovich.
- Sorry, Detective...?

02:24.560 --> 02:27.602
Mankovich. Frank.
Frank Mankovich. Detective.

02:27.685 --> 02:30.018
Don't let anybody through,
especially the press.

02:33.435 --> 02:35.393
- Detective Hankovich.
- Detective.

02:35.477 --> 02:39.393
Hey, we're part of the investigation.
Detective Frank Wankovich.

02:39.477 --> 02:42.143
Detective Claire Lady.
What happened here?

02:42.227 --> 02:44.268
I already told
all your colleagues everything.

02:44.352 --> 02:45.768
Well, you can tell me again, then.

02:47.185 --> 02:50.768
Well, I was by reception and a man
came in, and he was wearing a helmet

02:50.852 --> 02:53.143
and he had a gun with a silencer.

02:54.560 --> 02:55.893
Mm-hm. And then?

02:56.477 --> 02:59.768
Well, he pointed the gun at Mr. Ivanov

02:59.852 --> 03:02.602
and shouted something in Russian, I think.

03:03.935 --> 03:04.810
Then he shot him.

03:04.893 --> 03:06.768
- What did he look like?
- Bonneville.

03:10.060 --> 03:11.060
Superintendent.

03:11.893 --> 03:14.018
I'm not disturbing you,
I hope, Bonneville?

03:14.102 --> 03:15.268
Oh. Not at all.

03:16.102 --> 03:18.727
Oh. Claire Maddox,
Perry, head of homicide.

03:18.810 --> 03:21.727
- Hi.
- Get out of here. Both of you.

03:21.810 --> 03:24.685
Right now. Or I'll slap you in custody.

03:24.768 --> 03:28.102
- Wait, you're not a detective?
- No.

03:28.185 --> 03:31.393
My name is Frank, though.
This wasn't all a lie.

03:31.477 --> 03:33.143
We had some good times, right?

03:37.102 --> 03:40.602
- Detective, a comment, please?
- Okay, let them through.

03:41.310 --> 03:44.227
- Hey. What? What are you doing?
- He said let them through.

03:44.310 --> 03:46.185
- You don't let anybody through.
- Oh.

03:50.602 --> 03:51.935
Oh, I've gotta go, darling.

03:52.018 --> 03:54.060
- Get me the control room.
- They're on.

03:55.310 --> 03:57.852
- Hey.
<i>- So, you got a story, Frank?</i>

03:58.477 --> 04:00.352
"Russian Mafia Wars."
How's that sound?

04:01.060 --> 04:03.768
<i>Okay. Let's do it now.</i>

04:03.852 --> 04:07.352
<i>Standing by. And you're on.</i>

04:07.852 --> 04:11.727
At 8:45, Sergei Ivanov,
a.k.a. Three Fingers,

04:11.810 --> 04:14.685
a figure in the Russian Mafia,
left his room at the York Hotel.

04:14.768 --> 04:19.142
He'd just breakfasted on eggs, toast,
and a black coffee. His last breakfast.

04:20.101 --> 04:23.768
The sumptuous lifestyle
and escapades of Sergei Ivanov,

04:23.852 --> 04:26.768
mover and shaker in the nightclubs
of Manhattan and New Jersey...

04:26.852 --> 04:29.435
Two minutes in the hotel
and he comes out with a story.

04:29.518 --> 04:35.310
- A true artist. He's the best.
- He's certainly the best at what he does.

04:36.477 --> 04:41.227
...a war that has only just begun.
This is Frank Bonneville, 365 News.

04:43.727 --> 04:44.810
That was great.

04:45.852 --> 04:48.352
- You need any help?
- No, I'm fine. Won't be a minute.

04:55.518 --> 04:56.643
"Darling."

04:57.268 --> 05:00.102
- Who was that, then, your girlfriend?
- I'm married.

05:01.393 --> 05:03.018
Ah.

05:03.102 --> 05:04.768
So, it's his wife.

05:04.852 --> 05:07.768
- Yeah.
- Eh! He's a player.

05:07.852 --> 05:09.612
Aren't you, Finch? Huh?

05:09.685 --> 05:11.477
- Chick in every port?
- Nah.

05:29.727 --> 05:30.768
Oh.

05:35.560 --> 05:37.120
- You okay?
- Yeah, fine.

05:37.185 --> 05:38.393
You want a coffee?

05:38.477 --> 05:41.310
Yeah, can I get a skim-milk latte?

05:41.393 --> 05:43.977
- You on a diet?
- A bit, yeah.

05:44.060 --> 05:46.602
I had a medical,
and apparently I'm 25 percent fat.

05:46.685 --> 05:49.977
- Is that bad?
- Yeah. It's more than some snacks.

05:51.185 --> 05:52.560
Ooh!

05:52.643 --> 05:55.102
- Okay.
- See you later.

06:06.977 --> 06:08.227
There he is.

06:09.935 --> 06:11.227
Huh?

06:11.310 --> 06:12.893
Look at you.

06:12.977 --> 06:16.060
First reporter with the story, again.

06:16.852 --> 06:18.685
All other journalists
banned from the site.

06:19.643 --> 06:20.643
Ha!

06:21.935 --> 06:24.602
Oh, no, wait. What are these?

06:25.518 --> 06:29.810
"Impersonating an officer."
"Tampering with a crime scene."

06:29.893 --> 06:32.143
- I got results.
- You're not Dirty Harry!

06:34.102 --> 06:37.935
At best, you're an underachiever
at a local radio station.

06:38.018 --> 06:39.852
Often, a drunk underachiever.

06:39.935 --> 06:43.102
- Would you rather I didn't get the story?
- Than break the law? Yeah.

06:43.185 --> 06:46.268
Why break the law? Plenty of news
without having to break the law.

06:46.352 --> 06:48.810
If you run out,
make up a story about a lost dog.

06:48.893 --> 06:50.852
I made up a story
about being a detective.

06:50.935 --> 06:55.102
One more slip-up and you're fired.
This is coming from upstairs, not from me.

06:55.185 --> 06:57.560
They've had it.
They don't need this anymore.

06:57.643 --> 07:01.143
You're an arrogant, selfish hack
who survives

07:01.227 --> 07:03.643
because everyone thinks
you're a local celebrity.

07:04.352 --> 07:06.518
I can't fire you
because I don't like you.

07:06.602 --> 07:09.060
But I can fire you if you break the law

07:09.143 --> 07:13.310
or for the next thing you do
that breaks the rules.

07:13.393 --> 07:17.060
I so much as find out you used
a disabled toilet, goodbye.

07:17.143 --> 07:20.060
- That's ridiculous.
- Yeah, it's ridiculous.

07:20.143 --> 07:22.643
Go ahead, punk, make my day.

07:29.602 --> 07:31.852
- Will there be any celebrities?
- The girl who reads the weather

07:31.935 --> 07:33.560
- knows Al Roker.
- Will he be here?

07:33.643 --> 07:35.268
No. She might, though.

07:35.352 --> 07:37.893
Hey, Sacha.
This is my wife, Eleanor.

07:37.977 --> 07:39.643
- Oh, finally. Hi.
- Hi.

07:39.727 --> 07:42.268
- Many in?
- Uh, no. No, you're the first.

07:42.352 --> 07:43.685
- Someone has to be.
- Exactly.

07:43.768 --> 07:45.935
And it's nice to be here in time
to see the staff prepare

07:46.018 --> 07:47.477
for such a prestigious event.

07:49.727 --> 07:51.685
See you later. Okay, let's get in.

07:52.727 --> 07:54.268
- Hi.
- Hi.

07:54.352 --> 07:56.477
Hi.

07:56.560 --> 07:59.018
- Balloons.
- It's still sunny out.

07:59.102 --> 08:00.643
Well, it's nearly July, isn't it?

08:00.727 --> 08:03.560
- Doesn't get dark till 9:00.
- Imagine going out in the darkness.

08:03.643 --> 08:07.060
- You're the first here.
- Yeah, he doesn't like to be late.

08:07.143 --> 08:09.518
- Champagne?
- Don't mind if I do.

08:11.227 --> 08:12.852
There you go. Ah.

08:14.227 --> 08:15.268
Mm.

08:19.393 --> 08:22.560
So, what do you think
of my little radio station event?

08:22.643 --> 08:25.977
Well, I mean, if it was really your
radio station, it would be something.

08:26.060 --> 08:28.602
Well, I'm chief sound engineer.

08:28.685 --> 08:31.143
And if you consider
that radio is just sound,

08:31.227 --> 08:32.893
I'm sort of chief engineer, really.

08:32.977 --> 08:36.434
In one of the biggest
local radio stations around. Locally.

08:36.518 --> 08:39.018
It's just not what I thought
you'd still be doing at 50.

08:39.102 --> 08:40.768
- What do you mean?
- Radio.

08:42.227 --> 08:43.977
- Radio is like...
- It's what I love.

08:44.059 --> 08:45.518
Yeah, but it's just not very exciting.

08:45.602 --> 08:48.227
- You're joking.
- No, I'm not joking. But go on, tell me.

08:48.310 --> 08:50.935
What is the most exciting thing
that's happened this week?

08:51.018 --> 08:53.102
- Okay. Um...
- Okay.

08:53.185 --> 08:54.852
- Well, you decide.
- Okay.

08:54.935 --> 08:58.685
Is it that our omnibus podcast
just made top 50 on iTunes?

08:58.768 --> 08:59.643
Ooh.

08:59.727 --> 09:02.935
Or, is it that Jamie Oliver
popped in yesterday

09:03.018 --> 09:05.352
- to talk to Stig Arnold about fat kids?
- Is he gonna be here?

09:05.435 --> 09:09.310
- Stig's never missed a party yet. Heh.
- I meant Jamie Oliver.

09:09.393 --> 09:10.393
Who knows?

09:10.477 --> 09:12.852
- So, no, then?
- No. Definitely not.

09:14.143 --> 09:16.018
You meet Stig.

09:16.102 --> 09:18.685
You won't want to see Jamie Oliver
after you've met Stig.

09:22.185 --> 09:23.352
Sorry.

09:26.102 --> 09:28.852
Haven't you ever wanted to do
something extraordinary?

09:30.602 --> 09:32.643
- Finch.
- Hi.

09:32.727 --> 09:35.977
Um, this is Geoffrey Mallard,
the radio boss.

09:36.060 --> 09:38.643
- This is my wife, Eleanor.
- Pleasure to meet you.

09:38.727 --> 09:41.685
I've been looking for you.
Some lunatic took his family hostage.

09:41.768 --> 09:44.185
He's armed. I need you and Claire
to go and cover it.

09:44.268 --> 09:45.852
- Now?
- Yeah, I don't have a choice.

09:45.935 --> 09:47.727
You're the only guy around.

09:47.810 --> 09:50.768
- Where is Claire?
- She's on her way here. Nice to meet you.

09:50.852 --> 09:52.560
Okay, I'm so sorry, darling.

09:52.643 --> 09:55.310
No, no, no, you're not leaving me here.
I don't know anyone.

09:55.393 --> 09:58.268
I don't have a choice. He said
I'm the only guy that can do this.

09:58.352 --> 10:00.893
- He said you're the only guy around.
- He didn't literally mean

10:00.977 --> 10:04.393
I'm the only guy around. He meant
I'm the only guy around that can do this.

10:04.477 --> 10:06.677
- He's around, he couldn't do it.
- You don't know that.

10:06.727 --> 10:09.727
- Oh, come on. Look at him.
- You can't do this to me. Come on.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.185
- Shh.
- "Shh!"

10:11.268 --> 10:13.102
No. You know what? Forget it.
I'm going home.

10:13.185 --> 10:17.477
Please don't. Don't, please.
Just wait here and enjoy yourself

10:17.560 --> 10:19.727
and I'll whiz back,
and then we'll have a...

10:19.810 --> 10:21.977
- You're gonna be gone for hours.
- No.

10:22.060 --> 10:25.852
In these situations the police usually get
the gunman to the window really quickly

10:25.935 --> 10:29.102
and shoot him through the top lip,
and that takes out the brain stem,

10:29.185 --> 10:31.602
so there's no reflex... action.

10:34.477 --> 10:36.310
- Hi.
- Did you see Mallard?

10:36.393 --> 10:39.893
Yeah. Oh, uh, this is Claire Maddox.
This is my wife, Eleanor.

10:39.977 --> 10:42.560
- Nice to meet you.
- Yeah.

10:45.060 --> 10:46.393
- We should go.
- Yeah.

10:47.018 --> 10:48.477
- See you in the lobby.
- Yeah, okay.

10:51.352 --> 10:53.852
Who's this? Is this Tony?
Look at this guy.

10:54.893 --> 10:57.352
- Anyway...
- How are you?

10:57.435 --> 10:59.185
- I've gotta go.
- Okay, fine, go.

10:59.268 --> 11:01.227
- Yeah?
- Whatever.

11:01.310 --> 11:02.310
You'll be all right?

11:02.352 --> 11:05.310
- I'll see you soon. Okay.
- Okay, go if you're gonna go.

11:15.602 --> 11:18.227
- Hey, Frank.
- Hey.

11:28.852 --> 11:30.310
- Hi.
- Hey.

11:35.268 --> 11:39.352
Did you see Frank arrive,
acting like he thinks he's James Bond?

11:39.435 --> 11:42.352
Yeah. I think he's really cool.
He doesn't care about anything.

11:42.435 --> 11:44.185
Oh.

11:44.268 --> 11:46.060
- How is that cool?
- Hi.

11:46.143 --> 11:47.393
- Hi.
- Oh...

11:49.102 --> 11:50.435
I don't know, I just...

11:51.435 --> 11:53.352
I just mean...

11:53.435 --> 11:57.810
I think it would be cool to be
like that sometimes, you know?

11:57.893 --> 12:00.768
I care about everything,
and I try my best,

12:00.852 --> 12:05.477
but nothing much seems to happen.
It's because I'm boring.

12:06.352 --> 12:08.227
- Why do you say that?
- Because it's true.

12:08.310 --> 12:11.393
I... I've never done
anything extraordinary.

12:12.185 --> 12:13.935
I think that's why I play video games.

12:14.018 --> 12:16.018
Because they're more interesting
than my real life.

12:17.893 --> 12:19.935
- <i>Rebel Coup?</i>
- Yeah. Do you play?

12:20.602 --> 12:23.060
- I'm trying to cut down.
- Yeah, me, too.

12:24.518 --> 12:27.018
- Take that, sucker.
- Nice move.

12:27.977 --> 12:30.018
Mr. Bonneville. I love your work.

12:30.102 --> 12:33.352
- Champagne?
- Thank you. Cheers.

12:34.352 --> 12:37.143
You're the Frank Bonneville?

12:37.977 --> 12:40.143
- Apparently.
- I listen to you every day.

12:41.560 --> 12:43.643
- Really?
- I wouldn't miss it.

12:44.477 --> 12:46.435
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

12:49.852 --> 12:52.435
Mm.

12:55.268 --> 12:56.435
Alone?

12:59.893 --> 13:01.685
- Yeah.
- Me, too.

13:02.477 --> 13:04.852
It's a lonely life, radio.

13:04.935 --> 13:08.102
- Tell me about it.
- It's so unglamorous.

13:08.185 --> 13:11.227
Yes, I know.
I was just saying that to my... self.

13:12.268 --> 13:14.977
Let me guess. PR.

13:16.602 --> 13:19.352
Yes. Yes. How did you know?

13:19.435 --> 13:22.852
Well, come on. You're too attractive
for Human Resources.

13:22.935 --> 13:27.685
- And not bitter enough for management.
- That's nice. I'm flattered.

13:27.768 --> 13:30.185
Why radio? Why not TV
or something more stimulating?

13:30.268 --> 13:32.352
- It's what I love.
- Cheers.

13:32.435 --> 13:34.727
- It's what I hate.
- No. Come on.

13:34.810 --> 13:36.768
- Yeah.
- Oh, you are so good at it.

13:36.852 --> 13:38.602
- Like, you exude passion.
- No.

13:38.685 --> 13:40.445
- It really comes across.
- That's not passion.

13:40.518 --> 13:41.893
- Yeah.
- That's frustration.

13:42.977 --> 13:45.393
I'm destined for bigger things,
and I know it.

13:45.477 --> 13:49.852
So, in the meantime, it's just like
I'm a big fish in a little pond.

13:49.935 --> 13:53.018
- Yeah.
- A big... angry fish.

13:53.102 --> 13:58.102
- Yeah.
- Big, drunk, angry fish, in a tiny,

13:58.185 --> 14:00.727
- shitty little pond.
- No. You know what?

14:01.268 --> 14:04.227
- At least you're honest about it.
- Where's that got me? Nowhere.

14:04.310 --> 14:07.185
No more "Mr. Nice Guy," you know?
Here's to cheating.

14:14.560 --> 14:17.602
It sounds like you're right
in my ear, whispering sweet nothings.

14:17.685 --> 14:19.977
- It really does.
- Resonance is better if I hold the mic...

14:20.060 --> 14:22.185
Excuse me, hold on.

14:32.060 --> 14:34.977
- Nothing serious?
- Nothing serious.

14:35.060 --> 14:37.352
Let me ask you two questions.
First question:

14:37.435 --> 14:39.810
- Was that from your boyfriend?
- I don't have a boyfriend.

14:39.893 --> 14:43.102
- Second question: You live near here?
- About five minutes.

14:43.185 --> 14:44.227
Wanna go there now?

14:47.685 --> 14:51.810
Why did you ask how far it was
before you invited yourself back?

14:52.352 --> 14:55.643
If it had been a bit further away,
would that have been a deal breaker?

14:55.727 --> 14:57.935
Like, five minutes, "Yeah, sure."

14:58.018 --> 15:00.477
Half-hour, "Yeah, forget it,
it's too much of a hassle."

15:01.018 --> 15:03.643
- No. Wait, what?
- Forget it. Come on.

15:04.102 --> 15:06.268
Let's make a move
so you don't waste too much time.

15:22.227 --> 15:24.268
- Drink?
- Yeah, sure.

15:39.477 --> 15:41.852
Thanks. Good night. It was fun.

15:45.727 --> 15:49.185
Do you want my number,
or should I take yours?

15:49.268 --> 15:50.352
I don't think so.

15:51.102 --> 15:53.060
- You're married, right?
- How did you know?

15:53.143 --> 15:57.393
Call it intuition, but not many women
collect superhero toys.

15:57.852 --> 16:00.893
Apparently, they're not toys.
They are "collectibles."

16:00.977 --> 16:02.143
Mm-hm.

16:02.227 --> 16:05.393
And you're the one saying
I should leave at 2:30 in the morning.

16:09.185 --> 16:11.435
I don't always do this sort of thing,
you know?

16:11.518 --> 16:13.352
Hey, I'm not judging, I'm just...

16:13.435 --> 16:16.477
And if you knew I was married,
then you're as bad as me.

16:16.560 --> 16:17.602
Not really.

16:17.685 --> 16:19.685
I didn't tell your husband
I'd be faithful to him

16:19.768 --> 16:21.643
and stand by him in sickness and health,
blah, blah.

16:21.727 --> 16:23.607
- Again, not judging, just saying.
- Wait, wait.

16:23.643 --> 16:26.477
You don't know anything
about me or my husband.

16:26.935 --> 16:29.727
Only that you were just unfaithful to him,
and he doesn't know

16:29.810 --> 16:31.970
or you wouldn't be throwing me out
and being defensive.

16:32.018 --> 16:34.893
Okay, marriage doesn't always turn out
like you planned, okay?

16:34.977 --> 16:37.268
I mean, he hasn't exactly
fulfilled his promise.

16:37.352 --> 16:39.518
I thought he'd be something big
in entertainment by now

16:39.602 --> 16:41.810
and I'd be living in a mansion
in Beverly Hills.

16:42.477 --> 16:44.643
I'm pretty sure they drop that
from the vows now.

16:44.727 --> 16:46.018
As for throwing you out...

16:46.935 --> 16:50.352
I just suggested
that we exchange numbers, so...

16:50.435 --> 16:52.185
So we could do this again?

16:52.935 --> 16:55.768
I thought you didn't do
this sort of thing all the time.

16:55.852 --> 16:57.852
- Fuck off.
- Charming.

16:59.435 --> 17:00.643
Okay.

17:11.393 --> 17:13.102
Yep, thanks. Frank!

17:14.060 --> 17:17.685
Like ten percent bigger.
Better for my cheekbones, right?

17:17.768 --> 17:19.268
- Yeah.
- See that?

17:19.352 --> 17:22.435
Can I get a word? Now is good.

17:26.518 --> 17:27.518
Yep, have a seat.

17:28.852 --> 17:32.060
Something's cooking in Ecuador.
The intel's a little sketchy,

17:32.143 --> 17:35.227
but it looks like an uprising
could be underway.

17:35.310 --> 17:39.685
Rebel troops amassing, reports
of arms stockpiles, that kind of thing.

17:39.768 --> 17:42.518
They can't say exactly when
it's gonna blow, but it's gonna.

17:42.602 --> 17:44.560
- You interested?
- I'm gone.

17:44.643 --> 17:49.185
It's dangerous.
Drug gangs ruling the streets. With guns.

17:49.268 --> 17:52.477
Kidnapping tourists... journalists.

17:53.768 --> 17:56.227
Listen, if you're not feeling
as brave as you pretend...

17:58.060 --> 18:01.393
- ...tell me now.
- When do I go?

18:01.477 --> 18:03.143
This afternoon.

18:03.727 --> 18:06.352
- You wanna take Claire?
- No.

18:06.435 --> 18:09.268
Pointless having two journalists
on the spot.

18:09.352 --> 18:12.352
Remember last time I was in Pakistan,
I had transmission problems?

18:12.810 --> 18:14.935
- I should take a technician.
- All right.

18:15.810 --> 18:17.018
Let's see.

18:18.560 --> 18:20.643
- Finch is available.
- Fine.

18:20.727 --> 18:23.768
All right. Work it out with him. Let's go.

18:24.685 --> 18:26.477
Marie, I need two tickets to Quito.

18:31.727 --> 18:34.852
- You could stay here with us.
- That would be a pleasure.

18:34.935 --> 18:36.185
Thanks, guys.

18:37.352 --> 18:39.852
You're the closest thing to family
I've got, if I'm honest.

18:40.727 --> 18:42.560
I've always felt at home here.

18:43.185 --> 18:45.977
- Hoping it won't come to that.
- You're coming to Ecuador with me.

18:46.060 --> 18:48.977
Get your passport to admin.
They need details to clear entry papers.

