This is a good birthday present, isn't it?

01:08:04.185 --> 01:08:07.185
"Oh, sorry. Happy birthday.
You've gotta go to Quito after all."

01:08:13.560 --> 01:08:15.685
- Thanks for everything.
- Anytime.

01:08:16.935 --> 01:08:19.518
- If you hadn't been there...
- I was there.

01:08:20.393 --> 01:08:24.102
Sure. And don't worry about your car.
I'll get it back to you.

01:08:24.185 --> 01:08:26.518
Return safely, that's all I ask.

01:08:27.727 --> 01:08:29.727
You give those kidnappers hell.

01:08:29.810 --> 01:08:32.977
There aren't really... Yeah. Okay.

01:08:35.018 --> 01:08:37.227
- We gotta go.
- Okay.

01:08:44.393 --> 01:08:48.018
- You need money?
- We're on our way to get money.

01:08:48.102 --> 01:08:50.477
- I know where there's lots of money.
- Where?

01:08:59.393 --> 01:09:01.143
- She's in bed.
- I'll wait here.

01:09:01.227 --> 01:09:03.768
- It'll be all over in five minutes.
- Well, come in with me.

01:09:03.852 --> 01:09:05.727
- No, we agreed I wouldn't have to.
- Why?

01:09:05.810 --> 01:09:07.435
- We just did.
- But why did we?

01:09:07.518 --> 01:09:09.118
- No reason.
- Well, come in with me, then.

01:09:09.185 --> 01:09:10.625
- Okay, but don't wake her up.
- Shh.

01:09:18.768 --> 01:09:20.935
- Why do you even have a safe?
- In case I get burgled.

01:09:21.018 --> 01:09:24.602
I've got expensive comics.
I've always wanted one, as well.

01:09:24.685 --> 01:09:25.810
They're really cool.

01:09:36.560 --> 01:09:39.393
- How much shall I take?
- A few more, just in case.

01:09:44.060 --> 01:09:46.018
Hiya. Uh, surprise.

01:09:46.102 --> 01:09:49.602
Um, Frank Bonneville,
this is my wife, Eleanor.

01:09:50.143 --> 01:09:51.383
- Hi.
- What are you doing here?

01:09:51.435 --> 01:09:53.075
Aren't you glad that
we're alive and well?

01:09:54.102 --> 01:09:56.727
See what I mean?
You'd have more chance with her than me.

01:09:56.810 --> 01:09:58.185
- Definitely not.
- No.

01:09:58.768 --> 01:10:02.143
Before you explain why you're not being
held hostage in Ecuador, tell me,

01:10:02.227 --> 01:10:06.060
- why are you stealing my money?
- We need it, to, um,

01:10:06.143 --> 01:10:10.352
bribe our way into Ecuador. To...

01:10:10.435 --> 01:10:15.643
Because I threw away the tickets
and passports at the airport.

01:10:15.727 --> 01:10:17.167
- What do you mean?
- I didn't mean to.

01:10:17.227 --> 01:10:20.310
I thought I was throwing away the letter
that I wrote you. That, um...

01:10:20.393 --> 01:10:22.560
- What are you talking about?
- It's a long story.

01:10:22.643 --> 01:10:24.768
- It's not your money.
- Excuse me?

01:10:27.227 --> 01:10:30.518
It's not your money. People gave that
money so we wouldn't be in danger,

01:10:30.602 --> 01:10:32.602
but we're not in danger,
so it's their money,

01:10:32.685 --> 01:10:35.727
but they don't need to know that.
So, it's definitely not yours.

01:10:35.810 --> 01:10:39.268
So, now I got nothing again.
You ruin everything.

01:10:39.352 --> 01:10:41.935
Well, weren't you gonna spend it anyway,
to pay our ransom?

01:10:42.018 --> 01:10:45.310
Of course.
But, like, you clearly don't need it now.

01:10:45.393 --> 01:10:47.310
You don't care if we live or die.

01:10:47.977 --> 01:10:50.560
You're in your element.
All the fame, all the attention.

01:10:50.643 --> 01:10:54.060
So long as you're still in the picture,
but you can feel it all slipping away.

01:10:54.143 --> 01:10:56.227
That's why you wanna
hold on to all the cash.

01:10:56.310 --> 01:10:58.435
What? Like you're so perfect.

01:10:59.643 --> 01:11:02.227
Maybe it's time the world knew
a few home truths about you.

01:11:03.227 --> 01:11:05.185
I think they'd learn
even worse things about you.

01:11:06.102 --> 01:11:08.685
- I don't care.
- I think you would.

01:11:15.185 --> 01:11:19.227
Look, how about this?
Let's go 50-50.

01:11:20.018 --> 01:11:23.352
We take our share, get into Ecuador,
turn up at the American embassy,

01:11:23.435 --> 01:11:26.060
say we've been released,
you say you paid the ransom,

01:11:26.143 --> 01:11:28.393
- keep the cash.
- We'll need evidence I paid the ransom.

01:11:28.477 --> 01:11:31.143
We're the evidence. We were kidnapped,
and now we're free.

01:11:31.227 --> 01:11:34.602
They're not gonna expect receipts
from a bunch of Ecuadorian kidnappers.

01:11:34.685 --> 01:11:36.645
- Who did I give the money to?
- You didn't.

01:11:36.727 --> 01:11:41.227
You were told to leave it under a bridge
because you...

01:11:41.310 --> 01:11:44.310
didn't wanna involve the police,
because they told you they'd kill us.

01:11:44.393 --> 01:11:47.227
So, you just left the money
for collection under a bridge.

01:11:47.310 --> 01:11:49.185
- What bridge?
- "What bridge"? Any bridge.

01:11:49.268 --> 01:11:50.143
They'll check.

01:11:50.227 --> 01:11:53.027
They'll find no money there because
the bad men came and took the money

01:11:53.102 --> 01:11:55.977
and gave it to the bad men
that were kidnapping us. It works.

01:11:58.810 --> 01:12:00.143
Okay, done.

01:12:00.227 --> 01:12:01.810
- Yeah.
- Get out.

01:14:11.477 --> 01:14:14.018
Oh. Jesus Christ. What was that?

01:14:17.935 --> 01:14:18.935
Bugs.

01:14:30.935 --> 01:14:32.602
- Truck.
- There's a truck.

01:14:32.685 --> 01:14:34.518
Yo! Yo!

01:14:35.727 --> 01:14:37.477
Hi. Hi.

01:14:37.560 --> 01:14:40.018
Oh. Hey. Hi.

01:14:40.768 --> 01:14:41.810
Thanks for stopping.

01:14:41.893 --> 01:14:42.768
- Where you go?
- Quito.

01:14:42.852 --> 01:14:45.412
- We need to get to the embassy.
- We can pay you and everything.

01:14:45.560 --> 01:14:48.018
- Ah, Americanos.
- English.

01:14:48.102 --> 01:14:49.822
Although I have lived
and worked in America.

01:14:49.893 --> 01:14:51.693
- Doesn't need your life history.
- Want to eat?

01:14:51.768 --> 01:14:53.768
No, it's fine, we're going
straight to the embassy.

01:14:53.852 --> 01:14:56.227
Embassy a few hours away. I need to eat.

01:14:56.310 --> 01:14:58.352
- I know a good place.
- I'm quite hungry.

01:14:58.435 --> 01:15:01.102
- This guy needs to eat, so...
- Of course. Yeah.

01:15:01.185 --> 01:15:02.560
Okay. Let's go there.

01:15:05.602 --> 01:15:07.518
Brilliant, cheers.

01:15:30.310 --> 01:15:32.435
- It's good.
- Sure.

01:15:39.477 --> 01:15:41.685
Oh, God. Jazz.

01:15:47.227 --> 01:15:50.268
Oh, good. Not jazz after all.

01:15:52.477 --> 01:15:55.602
Hi. Hey. Oh. Nice.

01:15:57.227 --> 01:15:58.227
Morning.

01:15:59.227 --> 01:16:00.352
Hi.

01:16:00.768 --> 01:16:02.435
Hiya. Oh.

01:16:05.060 --> 01:16:07.060
Rustic, isn't it?

01:16:07.727 --> 01:16:09.167
No air-conditioning, though.

01:16:10.560 --> 01:16:12.977
Makes you drink more,
doesn't it? Crafty.

01:16:13.643 --> 01:16:16.602
- He looks like he's had enough.
- We're gonna eat and then leave.

01:16:16.685 --> 01:16:20.477
Sure. Shall I call for a menu?
Don't know who's working here.

01:16:20.560 --> 01:16:21.643
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:16:22.893 --> 01:16:25.393
- Americano?
- Uh, well, English.

01:16:25.477 --> 01:16:27.227
But I, um... Yeah.

01:16:28.477 --> 01:16:32.143
You look handsome. And rich.
You must be very successful.

01:16:32.227 --> 01:16:34.727
- I do okay, babe.
- Let's go.

01:16:34.810 --> 01:16:36.185
Uh, no.

01:16:36.810 --> 01:16:40.227
- But, you know, you look tired.
- I am tired.

01:16:40.310 --> 01:16:42.143
Do you want something to wake you up?

01:16:42.227 --> 01:16:43.102
- Sure.
- Okay.

01:16:43.185 --> 01:16:45.560
No. You sniff it.

01:16:47.893 --> 01:16:49.733
- What the fuck are you doing?
- You want some?

01:16:49.768 --> 01:16:51.143
- No, we're going.
- We're not going.

01:16:51.227 --> 01:16:52.977
- We're going!
- We're not going.

01:16:53.060 --> 01:16:55.477
Listen to me. My wife left me, okay?

01:16:55.560 --> 01:16:58.185
Presumably for someone better.
Who isn't better than me?

01:16:58.268 --> 01:17:01.602
Just having a bit of fun, to remind me
that life's worth living.

01:17:02.560 --> 01:17:03.852
Give me that, please.

01:17:05.977 --> 01:17:07.143
What the hell.

01:17:10.518 --> 01:17:11.518
Funny, isn't it?

01:17:13.185 --> 01:17:14.810
- Hello.
- Gentlemen.

01:17:14.893 --> 01:17:16.060
Hi.

01:17:16.143 --> 01:17:17.823
- So, you like the sample, eh?
- Thank you.

01:17:17.852 --> 01:17:20.185
- And now, you gotta buy.
- I knew it.

01:17:20.268 --> 01:17:21.685
That's fair enough.

01:17:21.768 --> 01:17:24.935
Gotta make a living. He's given us
a little free sample, you know.

01:17:25.018 --> 01:17:27.977
So, I'll have one.

01:17:28.352 --> 01:17:30.602
Thank you. Cheers.
There you go.

01:17:31.602 --> 01:17:33.643
I won't do it now.

01:17:33.727 --> 01:17:36.268
In fact, I think I'd better hide it.

01:17:36.352 --> 01:17:38.152
I don't want them finding this
at the embassy.

01:17:38.227 --> 01:17:39.810
Don't worry about it. They won't.

01:17:41.143 --> 01:17:42.893
- Shit.
- Come on, let's go, <i>papi.</i>

01:17:44.393 --> 01:17:45.685
Let's go, come on.

01:17:47.560 --> 01:17:48.810
- Move.
- Okay.

01:17:48.893 --> 01:17:50.060
- Come on, move!
- Okay.

01:17:50.143 --> 01:17:51.227
Move.

01:17:51.518 --> 01:17:52.602
All right.

01:17:52.685 --> 01:17:54.435
- Let's go.
- Move.

01:17:57.477 --> 01:17:58.643
Keep an eye on them.

01:18:27.602 --> 01:18:31.602
Get out. Let's go.
Let's go, get out. Move.

01:18:31.685 --> 01:18:32.685
Okay.

01:18:36.810 --> 01:18:38.852
Move. Hey!

01:18:44.143 --> 01:18:47.768
In there. Over there. Over there, move.
Now go. Go, go, go.

01:18:57.227 --> 01:18:59.727
- Look at this.
- Enjoy the view.

01:19:04.643 --> 01:19:07.643
Gotta love tourists.
They're nice people.

01:19:07.727 --> 01:19:09.268
- Very nice.
- Excuse me.

01:19:09.810 --> 01:19:12.643
There's no toilet... in here.

01:19:22.768 --> 01:19:25.102
- Sorry about this.
- Don't worry about it.

01:19:27.268 --> 01:19:28.935
What do you mean,
"don't worry about it"?

01:19:32.935 --> 01:19:34.977
I have to tell you something. Um...

01:19:37.852 --> 01:19:40.560
Probably gonna end up dying here,
and I don't wanna have to die

01:19:40.643 --> 01:19:42.810
- with this on my conscience, so...
- What now?

01:19:45.352 --> 01:19:46.477
I'm just gonna say it.

01:19:49.602 --> 01:19:52.768
I slept with your wife, Eleanor.

01:19:54.143 --> 01:19:57.393
- The night of the party.
- No, you didn't. What do you mean?

01:19:57.477 --> 01:20:00.102
- I didn't know who she was.
- You're serious?

01:20:00.185 --> 01:20:01.602
I didn't know she was your wife.

01:20:05.810 --> 01:20:09.393
How do you think that makes me feel?
That my wife just...

01:20:09.477 --> 01:20:10.852
- has it off with anyone?
- Hardly.

01:20:10.935 --> 01:20:13.935
The first smarmy bastard who comes along.

01:20:14.018 --> 01:20:18.227
Just a big phony and a liar and a cheat.
Oh, I feel sick.

01:20:21.852 --> 01:20:24.227
So, you've been laughing at me
behind my back all this time.

01:20:24.310 --> 01:20:27.060
No, not at all. I felt terrible
when I found out. I like you.

01:20:27.143 --> 01:20:30.685
- You got a funny way of showing it.
- I did not know she was your wife.

01:20:30.768 --> 01:20:32.393
- So you keep saying.
- She's the one to blame.

01:20:32.477 --> 01:20:35.685
She knew she was married to you.
She chose not to share that with me.

01:20:38.018 --> 01:20:40.060
So, you wouldn't have done it
if you had known?

01:20:40.143 --> 01:20:43.185
Of course not. What do you think of me?

01:20:43.268 --> 01:20:46.060
Maybe she'll really
try and get us out now.

01:20:46.143 --> 01:20:48.810
She'll be killing two birds
with one stone, won't she?

01:20:48.893 --> 01:20:50.852
She'll be getting her husband back
and her lover.

01:21:10.768 --> 01:21:11.852
Morning.

01:21:14.018 --> 01:21:17.602
Hey, man, I'm sorry. I wouldn't have said
anything. I thought you were over her.

01:21:17.685 --> 01:21:21.477
I am over her, so, don't say anything.
Let's just get through this.

01:21:28.768 --> 01:21:29.768
You okay?

01:21:32.893 --> 01:21:34.018
Go.

01:21:40.477 --> 01:21:41.685
- Thank you.
- Mm-hm.

01:21:41.768 --> 01:21:43.685
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

01:21:43.768 --> 01:21:46.518
- Have you got any bread?
- It's not room service.

01:21:47.143 --> 01:21:49.602
- Are you a prisoner, too?
- Of course he's a prisoner.

01:21:49.685 --> 01:21:51.935
- Maybe he can help.
- He can't help, look at him.

01:21:52.018 --> 01:21:54.352
He is helping us.
He brought us food, didn't he?

01:21:54.435 --> 01:21:57.935
- Let him go. He's terrified.
- Okay. Thank you.

01:22:04.310 --> 01:22:05.477
Chili for breakfast.

01:22:08.685 --> 01:22:10.435
Oh. It's really hot as well.

01:22:10.518 --> 01:22:12.602
Mm.

01:22:25.185 --> 01:22:27.145
If you hold your nose,
you can't taste it as much.

01:22:27.227 --> 01:22:28.768
Really?

01:22:30.143 --> 01:22:32.477
- Who do you think these people are?
- They're bandits.

01:22:32.560 --> 01:22:33.893
They're gonna ask for ransom.

01:22:33.977 --> 01:22:36.060
- Who's gonna pay that?
- I don't know. Government?

01:22:36.143 --> 01:22:37.863
- Not the U.S. government.
- What do you mean?

01:22:37.935 --> 01:22:39.735
- They don't negotiate with terrorists.
- Why?

01:22:45.685 --> 01:22:47.518
- Journalist, okay?
- Yeah.

01:22:47.602 --> 01:22:51.518
- And you?
- No. Uh, I'm a technician.

01:22:51.602 --> 01:22:54.310
- Is your boss rich?
- No, not at all.

01:22:54.393 --> 01:22:56.935
- Is your family rich?
- No.

01:22:57.643 --> 01:23:01.477
My wife has got cash, at the moment.

01:23:02.185 --> 01:23:03.685
- She has, she's got loads.
- Your wife?

01:23:03.768 --> 01:23:07.060
Mm. She'll pay, then you'll release us,
yeah? Unharmed.

01:23:07.143 --> 01:23:09.268
- Yeah, of course.
- Don't... Yeah. Okay.

01:23:09.352 --> 01:23:12.185
You're gonna call your wife, okay?

01:23:12.268 --> 01:23:13.518
- Okay.
- Call her.

01:23:13.602 --> 01:23:16.893
- She's never gonna believe him.
- Shh. Let's keep it positive.

01:23:17.810 --> 01:23:19.810
- What do you say to him?
- Call your wife.

01:23:19.893 --> 01:23:22.143
- Good. Good.
- I am.

01:23:22.227 --> 01:23:25.935
- How much money do you want?
- 100,000 for each of you.

01:23:26.018 --> 01:23:27.518
- That's a lot.
- Shh.

01:23:27.602 --> 01:23:28.893
Well, it is. I'm saying.

01:23:28.977 --> 01:23:31.643
I'm not gonna promise anything,
but we're gonna get you what...

01:23:41.560 --> 01:23:43.852
- Hello?
<i>- Eleanor.</i>

01:23:44.435 --> 01:23:47.102
- What do you want?
- Right, we're in Ecuador,

01:23:47.185 --> 01:23:52.685
and we've been captured by bandits
and they want $200,000

01:23:52.768 --> 01:23:56.143
<i>- or they're gonna kill me and Frank.</i>
- Stop it. Where are you calling me from?

01:23:57.060 --> 01:23:59.643
- Where are we exactly? She wants to know.
- $300,000.

01:23:59.727 --> 01:24:03.102
Hear that? He put it up. That's what
we're dealing with, unreasonable.

01:24:03.185 --> 01:24:05.727
Do you think I'm an idiot?
I'm keeping that money.

01:24:05.810 --> 01:24:08.727
I raised it, I gave you your half.
Stop trying to con me out of mine.

01:24:08.810 --> 01:24:10.935
She thinks we're conning her.
She doesn't believe me.

01:24:11.018 --> 01:24:13.518
- She thinks we're trying to get her money.
- She doesn't trust him.

01:24:13.602 --> 01:24:15.602
- You gotta talk to her.
- You talk to her.

01:24:15.643 --> 01:24:18.685
- Talk to her, please.
- I'm gonna hand you to the head bandit.

01:24:18.768 --> 01:24:21.560
<i>Bandido. </i> So, you speak to her.

01:24:23.477 --> 01:24:24.977
- Hello, ma'am.
- Eleanor.

01:24:25.518 --> 01:24:27.102
- What's that?
- Eleanor.

01:24:27.185 --> 01:24:28.393
Eleanor.

01:24:29.018 --> 01:24:34.310
Eleanor, if you don't pay, I'm gonna
kill your husband and Mr. Franks.

01:24:36.060 --> 01:24:38.727
Kill everybody. Greetings from New York.

01:24:40.977 --> 01:24:44.227
- What'd she say?
- She said to kill you all.

01:24:45.727 --> 01:24:47.435
- She said that?
- She said that, yeah.

01:24:47.518 --> 01:24:49.318
- That's what I'm dealing with.
- Who is this?

01:24:49.685 --> 01:24:51.893
- That's my wife.
- Your wife makes me very sad.

01:24:51.977 --> 01:24:54.817
Welcome to my world, son. I'm glad
you spoke to her, though, first-hand.

01:24:54.893 --> 01:24:56.685
- Urgh!
- I know. She's...

01:24:56.768 --> 01:24:58.102
Yeah.

01:25:03.185 --> 01:25:04.602
That's nice, isn't it? "Kill them."

01:25:04.685 --> 01:25:07.602
I can't believe she just did that.
She hung up?

01:25:07.685 --> 01:25:09.045
She said, "Kill them." And then...

01:25:12.227 --> 01:25:14.947
- We gotta be professional.
- I was professional.

01:25:15.018 --> 01:25:16.560
You were not professional.

01:25:16.643 --> 01:25:18.403
I did exactly what you told me to.

01:25:20.518 --> 01:25:21.518
Thank you.

01:25:25.643 --> 01:25:27.560
What the fuck did you just do?

01:25:28.352 --> 01:25:29.685
Hey, come on. Hey!

01:25:29.768 --> 01:25:32.102
- No, no, no. Is okay. Is okay.
- Sorry.

01:25:35.185 --> 01:25:37.560
- Who the fuck are you talking to?
- Nothing.

01:25:38.060 --> 01:25:39.852
He's sorry. We're sorry. Sorry.

01:25:57.893 --> 01:26:01.185
- What are you thinking?
- Thinking that chili was definitely off.

01:26:01.893 --> 01:26:08.102
Speed of sound is about
350 meters per second, a bit less.

01:26:09.143 --> 01:26:13.185
A bullet is about 400 meters per second.

01:26:15.852 --> 01:26:20.227
So, if they shoot us,
we'll be dead before we hear the bang.

01:26:20.810 --> 01:26:23.727
- Great. So, we won't jump, then.
- No.

01:26:25.768 --> 01:26:29.143
- I'm scared.
- You weren't yesterday, in the bar.

01:26:29.227 --> 01:26:30.560
That was the cocaine.

01:26:37.602 --> 01:26:38.643
Look.

01:26:39.643 --> 01:26:43.060
Maybe this will make me
a little bit braver again.

01:26:43.143 --> 01:26:44.227
Popeye on spinach.

01:26:50.852 --> 01:26:52.018
Where is it?

01:26:53.018 --> 01:26:55.143
Your sweat probably dissolved it.

01:27:01.643 --> 01:27:07.268
- I can taste it. Do you want some?
- Yeah. Why don't I suck your toes, too?

01:27:08.018 --> 01:27:09.060
No.

